Gunmen, on New Year’s Eve, attacked a passenger boat in Bayelsa State. According to the report, the boat, carrying 14 passengers left Yenagoa en route to Twon-Brass in Brass Local Government Area of the state when the gunmen struck. It was learnt that the gunmen made away with the 115-horsepower Yamaha outboard engine of the boat and dispossessed the passengers of their valuables.   A’Ibom APC chieftain shot dead on New Year Day     Bandits release two more Baptist students     Bandits kill 7, abduct 18 in attacks on Kaduna villages   The Bayelsa Chairman of the Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria, Mr Ogoniba Ipigansi, told reporters in Yenagoa yesterday that the passengers were left unhurt, however. “The gunmen dumped the driver and the passengers in the bush before carting away the outboard engine,” he said. - Advertisement - Ipigansi also said a rescue team had been dispatched to the scene of the incident.